The nature of big data and its potential for solving complex problems. Field courses related to big data. The Nature of the Data Industry. models, regulations.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to define big data and data industry, explain its structure, resources, value chain, services in different domains and sectors, but also business models in data industry and developing models of data industry. The course also reviews emerging regulation forms of data industry and connects real-time policymaking options and data industry.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course student: * Understands the implications of big data and the data industry on public sector governance and economic policy making; * Can see the possibilities of applying big data analysis to solve complex problems in specific areas of the public sector; * Has an overview of the various challenges and risks associated with the use of big data; * Can evaluate the volumes and developments of the data industry and find cooperation partners; * Acquires contacts with technology companies and researchers from other fields (medicine, IT, robotics, environment)
